The TiVo(R) Newsletter
PAUSE-Worthy News
Volume 26
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Transfer Service to a Series2!
To reward you, our original subscriber, for your
tireless loyalty and support, we're launching
the Switch-to-Series2 Upgrade Offer*, giving you
the one-time opportunity to transfer product
lifetime service from your original TiVo DVR to
a new TiVo Series2**. Gear up for Home Media Option
and take advantage of this limited-time offer today.
Go to www.tivo.com/upgrade to learn more!
http://r.4at1.com/c/e/r/r.jsp?rid=163.7468.509798.233568.25435.424.52539759.0.2

Learn more about Home Media Option:
http://r.4at1.com/c/e/r/r.jsp?rid=163.7468.509798.233568.25436.424.52539759.0.2



TiVo Tip: TiVo Tunes In
Until someone comes up with a "TiVo" for radio
(because wouldn't it be great if your radio
automatically tuned to any station playing your
favorite artist the minute said artist goes "live
on air"?), know that you've already got the next
best thing: Get in the groove by entering your
favorite musical artist as a WishList keyword search.
Use the PAUSE button for quotation marks to indicate
exact phrase. For example, enter [PAUSE button] FRANK
[Use FWD. button for space] SINATRA [PAUSE button]
and select "Auto-record episodes." (This trick often
unearths incredible musical guest performances from
the archives of "Saturday Night Live.") Or for general
music enthusiasts who like a little Salsa with all that
Jazz, try this tip: From TiVo Central, select "Pick
Programs to Record," then "Search Using WishList,"
then select "Category." Choose "Arts" as a category,
"Music" as a sub-category, then "View upcoming episodes."
See what strikes a chord and schedule recordings as the
music moves you! How's that for ending on a high note?



You Ask. we Answer.
Q. Nicole W. asks, "When the Home Media Option is
released, do I have to pay for the whole package to
use just the features I want? Also, will Home Media
Option be available on all TiVo DVRs, or just the Series2?"

A. Good questions, Nicole. In short, the answers are
yes and no respectively, but let's review each in more
detail.

By definition, Home Media Option is a bundled premium
package that includes four new features in networked
home entertainment: digital photos, digital music,
remote scheduling and multi-room viewing. So, yes,
Home Media Option is sold only in its entirety and
requires a one-time registration fee of $99 for the
first TiVo Series2 DVR.**** Additional TiVo Series2 DVRs
on the same account require a discounted one-time
registration fee of $49. Once a DVR is registered with
Home Media Option, that DVR is eligible to make use of
all four features. So to answer your question more
specifically, Home Media Option features will not be
sold a la carte. But they'll all be available. Try them
out, you may be surprised! 

Which leads us to your second question: No, not all
TiVo DVRs are enabled for Home Media Option. The four
features within Home Media Option will only be functional
on a TiVo Series2 DVR. Why? Because Home Media Option
requires the latest hardware design of the TiVo Series2,
including USB ports that enable easy, plug-and-play
networking opportunities in the home. 

Home Media Option is a fantastic foray into the world of
networked home entertainment and a natural enhancement
to all advanced digital recording services. But Home
Media Option remains exactly that: an option. If you
already have an always-on Internet connection at home
(DSL, cable modem, ISDN, etc.), and find yourself wishing
you could schedule a recording for your TiVo DVR while
still in the office, paying the one-time registration
fee of $99 might be well worth the money, even if that's
the only feature that interests you. Or music. Or photos.
Or multi-room viewing. There's a lot of good stuff there!

Oh, and one more thing: Once Home Media Option becomes
available, all subscribers with a TiVo Series2 will be
able to connect to the TiVo service using their always-on
Internet connection from home. And that's whether or not
you choose to purchase the premium package. (A standard
phone line is still required for your initial call during
Guided [or Repeat Guided] Setup.)

Learn more about all four features bundled together in the
TiVo Home Media Option premium package.
http://r.4at1.com/c/e/r/r.jsp?rid=163.7468.509798.233568.25436.424.52539759.0.2



Did you know...?
...that "Trading Spaces," the remodeling show where neighbors
impose their decorating tastes on neighbors, is an American
twist on a British show called "Changing Rooms"? Find it on
BBC America. And here's a funny turn on that twist: last year,
a poll conducted for HGTV revealed that TV viewers ranked
"Trading Spaces" one of their favorite programs on the cable
channel. But guess what? You'll find the home improvement show
on TLC, not HGTV. Not the sharpest tools in the tool shed, eh?
Or maybe they just have TiVo! 



Home Media Option(TM): Remote Scheduling
Last newsletter, we highlighted Digital Music and Digital Photos,
two of the four new networked home entertainment features that
will be bundled together in Home Media Option, a premium package
for TiVo Series2 subscribers. Now, we'll spotlight the third
feature: Remote Scheduling from the web. Register your TiVo
Series2 DVR with Home Media Option and you'll be able to schedule
recordings from anywhere you have Internet access! How does it
work? You'll just go to tivo.com and schedule recordings online.
You'll be able to search for a show by time, title, keyword,
category, or actor/director and set up a single or Season Pass(TM)
recording, complete with all of the recording options. With remote
scheduling, it's never been easier to tell your TiVo DVR the shows
you don't want to miss, whether you're on the couch or in the
office. Next newsletter, we'll highlight the fourth component of
Home Media Option: Multi-room Viewing. Sign up to receive an
e-mail alert the minute Home Media Option becomes available!
http://www.tivo.com/jump/sub.asp?n=26&URL=0.9.1.asp?email=nospam@mailshell.com



I Heart (or is it Hart?) TV
How's this for Valentine's Day TV viewing: Stars like Jennifer
Lopez, George Clooney and Oprah Winfrey recounting their first
times...as subjects on "Entertainment Tonight." "The Stars'
First Time...On Entertainment Tonight With Mary Hart" will
air Feb. 14 at 8 p.m. Among the highlights of the one-hour
special, Hart told Variety, is Winfrey's original interview.
"She said, 'I know I made it now...I'm on 'Entertainment Tonight,'
and exuberantly sings the 'ET' theme song." Hart's husband,
Burt Sugarman, came up with the idea and will serve as an
executive producer.



WishList Searches Revisited
So subscriber Joan got her wish for the addition of "Figure
Skating" and Steve will surely jump when he sees "Cricket,"
but all of us will benefit from the new and improved system
now available on your TiVo DVR*** that categorizes television
programs into genres. These changes will deliver more refined
search results when you Search by Title or Create a WishList,
making it even easier for you to find the shows you don't want
to miss.

So, if you have existing WishList searches, please take a
moment to review the categories and subcategories selected.
In some instances, you may need to re-create them with the
new options. Here's a quick summary of the changes:
1) Fifty-nine new sports sub-categories were added. Woo-hoo!
The five most popular sports are now at the top, with the
remaining 88 alphabetized below. 2) Twenty-two brand-new
genres were added. Find them in "Interests," "Science and
Nature," and "News and Business." 3) The category "Arts &
Living" was renamed "Interests." 4) The category "Western"
was removed from the top level and the category "Arts" was
added. "Western" was placed under "Interests" as a sub-category
and eight arts-related genres, like "Music," were moved from
"Interests" to the new category "Arts." Whew! To create new
or edit existing WishList searches, simply: Go to TiVo Central
by pressing the TiVo button on your remote control, then
SELECT "Pick Programs to Record," then SELECT "Search Using
WishList."



