                <td width="20" align="left">&nbsp;</td>
                <td width="259"> 
                  <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">So subscriber 
                    Joan got her wish for the addition of &quot;Figure Skating&quot; 
                    and Steve will surely jump when he sees &quot;Cricket,&quot; 
                    but all of us will benefit from the new and improved system 
                    now available on your TiVo DVR*** that categorizes television 
                    programs into genres. These changes will deliver more refined 
                    search results when you Search by Title or Create a WishList, 
                    making it even easier for you to find the shows you don't 
                    want to miss.</font></p>
                  <p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">So, if 
                    you have existing WishList searches, please take a moment 
                    to review the categories and subcategories selected. In some 
                    instances, you may need to re-create them with the new options. 
                    Here's a quick summary of the changes: 1) Fifty-nine new sports 
                    sub-categories were added. Woo-hoo! The five most popular 
                    sports are now at the top, with the remaining 88 alphabetized 
                    below. 2) Twenty-two brand-new genres were added. Find them 
                    in &quot;Interests,&quot; &quot;Science and Nature,&quot; 
                    and &quot;News and Business.&quot; 3) The category &quot;Arts 
                    &amp; Living&quot; was renamed &quot;Interests.&quot; 4) The 
                    category &quot;Western&quot; was removed from the top level 
                    and the category &quot;Arts&quot; was added. &quot;Western&quot; 
                    was placed under &quot;Interests&quot; as a sub-category and 
                    eight arts-related genres, like &quot;Music,&quot; were moved 
                    from &quot;Interests&quot; to the new category &quot;Arts.&quot; 
                    Whew! To create new or edit existing WishList searches, simply: 
                    Go to TiVo Central by pressing the TiVo button on your remote 
                    control, then SELECT &quot;Pick Programs to Record,&quot; 
                    then SELECT &quot;Search Using WishList.&quot;</font></p></td>
